==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oxamide
<hw>Ox*am"ide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n</pos>, <ety>[<ets>Ox</ets>alic +
<ets>amide</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline
neutral substance (<chform>C2O2(NH2)2)</chform> obtained by treating
ethyl oxalate with ammonia. It is the acid amide of oxalic acid.
Formerly called also <altname>oxalamide</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxamidine</ent>⟦br⟧
